      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson introduces how artificial intelligence is being used in food safety monitoring, including hygiene inspections and compliance checks across the food industry. While AI tools can offer speed and consistency, it is important to understand the risks that come with relying on them too heavily in high risk environments. We will explore real-world scenarios where AI may fall short, such as misidentifying contamination risks or failing to account for context that a trained human inspector would recognise. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of where AI can support food safety processes and where human oversight remains essential. No prior knowledge of AI or food safety regulations is required, making this lesson accessible to anyone working in or around the food industry.",
